FT  08 MAY 92 / Bill to endorse treaties published
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PHILIP STEPHENS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE government yesterday published the short bill that will implement the
Maastricht agreement on economic and political union, Philip Stephens
writes.
The bill makes clear that a separate decision by parliament would be
required before sterling could be absorbed into a single European currency.
It also signalled its determination to press ahead quickly with preparations
to put in place its privatisation programme with the publication of the bill
to pave the way for eventual sell-off of British Coal and British Rail.
The British Coal and British Rail (Transfer Proposals) Bill empowers the two
corporations to take whatever steps are necessary to prepare for
privatisation. It will be followed, probably in the autumn, with separate
bills providing for the implementation of plans for the sale of British Coal
and for private operation of train services.
A third bill tabled yesterday will implement the changes to the Uniform
Business Rate announced in the Budget.
