FT  08 MAY 92 / Arts: Royal Ballet new season
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANTONY THORNCROFT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The Royal Ballet is staging Tales of Beatrix Potter at Covent Garden next
December. This is the first time that the work, choreographed by Frederick
Ashton for a movie in 1971, has been performed live. Anthony Dowell,
director of the Royal Ballet, has undertaken the adaptation which should
prove a success for the company.
The other major ballets in the 1992-93 season are the British premiere of
Baryshnikov's Don Quixote and a new one act ballet by David Bintley designed
by Jasper Conran. The Royal Ballet will dance Glen Tetley's La Ronde for the
first time and there will be a new production of Balanchine's Ballet
Imperial.
General director Jeremy Isaacs confirmed yesterday that Covent Garden will
close in 1997 for large scale renovation work. It hopes to be a beneficiary
of the Government's Millennium Fund and open its refurbished building in
grand style to welcome the 21st century.
