<HEADLINE>
FT  07 MAY 92 / (CORRECTED) People: Insurance moves
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Correction (published 26th May 1992) appended to this article.
Graham Ford is leaving Brown Shipley Insurance Brokers to launch a new
national insurance broking venture. Ford, now 52, has been closely
identified with the growth of the Brown Shipley broking business and had
been involved in efforts to lead a management buy-out. After the failure of
these, however, Ford has joined forces with Merseyside-based Berkeley Burke
and Manson Reed, a broker which specialises in meeting the needs of sport
centres, bowling alleys and other leisure installations. Ford will be
managing director of the new venture, which is to be known as Burke Ford
Reed Insurance Management. The group hopes to obtain a full Lloyd's
registration within 18 months.
*****
Michael Kier is to become chairman of CE HEATH on the retirement in July of
Richard Fielding. John MacKenzie Green, group md, will become chairman of CE
Heath (Insurance Broking).
*****
Ralph Sneddon has been appointed md of BAIN CLARKSON's continental Europe
operations; he joins from Sedgwick.
*****
Roger Cooper has been appointed a director of BALLANTYNE, McKEAN &amp; SULLIVAN;
Charles Simpson has been appointed a director of its subsidiary BMS LMX.
*****
John Clayton has been appointed company secretary of GUARDIAN ROYAL EXCHANGE
on the retirement of John Evans.
Correction (published 26th May 1992)
The FT stated on May 7 that Burke Ford Reed Insurance Management had 'joined
forces with Berkeley Burke'. This was incorrect. Burke Ford Reed has linked
up with Berkeley Burke Northern Group, a former subsidiary of the Berkeley
Burke Group, which also conducts insurance broking business and continues to
trade independently.
</TEXT>
