FT  07 MAY 92 / International Company News: Wesfarmers climbs 77%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KEVIN BROWN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
WESFARMERS, the diversified Australian agricultural group, yesterday said it
was confident of meeting its full-year net profit target of ADollars 60m
(USDollars 45.4m) after reporting a 77 per cent increase in profits to
ADollars 38m for the first nine months, writes Kevin Brown in Sydney. Sales
were up from ADollars 877m to ADollars 984m.
The group said lower interest rates and greater efficiency in the
fertilisers and chemicals division contributed towards the better
performance. In addition, fertiliser sales were higher than in the
comparable period of last year.
Wesfarmers said demand for cropping fertilisers grew strongly in response to
improved wheat prices. The coal, dairy and retail operations contributed
improved results, while profits from the gas and transport operations
remained steady.
The group said it was confident of meeting its full-year profit target, but
warned the result was difficult to predict because of the possible effect of
weather between April and June, when most fertiliser sales take place.
