<TEXT>
WOOLWORTH, the US retailer, yesterday reported a small Dollars 17m profit
after-tax in the three months to April 25. This compares with a Dollars 100m
loss a year earlier, but the 1991 figure was struck after an
accounting-related charge of Dollars 100m, writes Nikki Tait in New York.
