<TEXT>
USAIR said it has reached a tentative agreement with the Air Line Pilots
Association on a four-year contract, Reuter reports.
The company said the agreement calls for immediate salary reductions for a
12-month period, 'considerable improvements in pilot productivity and cost
savings in health care', which will provide USAir with short-term cost
savings.
It said pilots would receive a series of pay increases at the beginning of
September, 1993.
USAir said the tentative deal would be submitted to the ALPA executive
committee for ratification on May 13.
It said it would provide no further details until then.
