FT  07 MAY 92 / UK Company News: LIT recovers to Pounds 1.29m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The strength of its UK operations helped LIT Holdings to produce a much
improved result for 1991.
Pre-tax profit of Pounds 1.29m for the year compared with a loss of Pounds
344,000 in 1990 for this financial services group.
Turnover was Pounds 83m (Pounds 91.1m) but operating profits from Johnson
Fry rose 50 per cent from Pounds 1.59m to Pounds 2.4m and LIT America
contributed Pounds 2.39m (Pounds 2.52m).
Both businesses are seasonal, so the bulk of profits were accrued in the
first half when the pre-tax profit was higher at Pounds 1.92m (Pounds
838,000).
Central charges fell to Pounds 3.5m (Pounds 4.45m) benefiting from the
refinancing of short-term debt into medium-term debt and redeemable
preference shares. Dividend payments on these shares took Pounds 203,000
after which losses per share were reduced to 1.4p (3p).
