<HEADLINE>
FT  07 MAY 92 / Pit may be sold to rival bidder
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BRITISH COAL is to turn to the rival bidder in the competition to reopen
Monktonhall colliery near Edinburgh after a consortium of mineworkers failed
to produce the finance needed to operate the pit.
It will invite Caledonian Mining, based at Newark, Notts, to pursue its
interest.
