FT  07 MAY 92 / The Queen's Speech: Urban regeneration agency - Main Points
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
An urban regeneration agency will be set up to co-ordinate the regeneration
of England's inner cities. It will aim to bring back into use vacant and
under-used land, and will have compulsory purchase powers similar to those
of existing urban development corporations.
The rents-to-mortgages proposals also contained in the bill will offer
council tenants a chance to become part-owners of their homes.
