FT  07 MAY 92 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Wool prices for wool at recent auctions have been almost static. After
dipping very slightly when sales were resumed after Easter the Australian
Wool Corporation's market indicator has stabilised at 577 cents a kg. This
is said to be around 100 cents below the level needed for woolgrowers to be
persuaded to maintain output and forecasts at present indicate a further
decline next season. The absence of any clear direction in the market as the
selling season draws to its close in June is causing quiet trading
throughout. The recession is showing slight signs of lifting in the severely
affected sectors.
