<DATE>920507
</DATE>
<HEADLINE>
FT  07 MAY 92 / International Capital Markets: Danish overseas debt set to
fall
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   COPENHAGEN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
DENMARK's overseas state debt is expected to fall to DKr77bn at the end of
the year from DKr92.3bn at end-1991, provided the current account remains in
surplus and private capital movements are at worst in balance, Reuter
reports from Copenhagen. The central bank said the share of
dollar-denominated debt rose to 19 per cent from 13 per cent in 1990 and
that of Ecu debts rose to 20 per cent from 15 per cent.
</TEXT>
